ow to cool completely, then transfer into a sealable container until ready to use."},{"content":"Remove puddings from refrigerator, spoon 1-2 teaspoons passionfruit pulp over each pudding, top with 1-2 tablespoons Greek yoghurt and sprinkle with nut topping to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the fresh mango with frozen, defrosted mango and fresh passionfruit pulp with canned or jarred passionfruit pulp in this recipe.","These puddings are a great \"on the go\" breakfast option. You can make the pudding the night before (through step 2) and store in sealable jars or containers in the refrigerator overnight. Simply add the toppings in the morning before you leave the house.","The chia seeds and nuts provide zinc, and the yoghurt and almonds are sources of calcium."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 15m","8 portions"]}